WEBVTT

1.1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.649
One flow.

1.2
00:00:03.649 --> 00:00:07.299
Two channels.

1.3
00:00:07.299 --> 00:00:10.948
Whether you're on a call or standing in the showroom, the logic of a Magppie pitch never changes.

2.1
00:00:10.948 --> 00:00:13.420
Eight stages.

2.2
00:00:13.420 --> 00:00:15.893
Open.

2.3
00:00:15.893 --> 00:00:18.365
Discover.

2.4
00:00:18.365 --> 00:00:20.838
Agitate the real problem.

2.5
00:00:20.838 --> 00:00:23.310
Introduce the solution.

2.6
00:00:23.310 --> 00:00:25.783
Go deep on the product.

2.7
00:00:25.783 --> 00:00:28.255
Qualify the budget — before any number.

2.8
00:00:28.255 --> 00:00:30.728
Price with confidence.

2.9
00:00:30.728 --> 00:00:33.200
And close on a concrete next step.

3.1
00:00:33.200 --> 00:00:37.775
The opening earns two minutes: introduce yourself, confirm it's a good time — then pause.

3.2
00:00:37.775 --> 00:00:42.350
Genuinely pause.

3.3
00:00:42.350 --> 00:00:46.926
Then discover three things: their city, for serviceability.

3.4
00:00:46.926 --> 00:00:51.501
Own home or investment, for budget context.

3.5
00:00:51.501 --> 00:00:56.076
And whether a designer is involved, for coordination.

4.1
00:00:56.076 --> 00:01:01.424
Then the truth most customers have never heard: most regular wooden kitchens have hidden issues — termites, mould, sagging.

4.2
00:01:01.424 --> 00:01:06.772
And the one nobody can see: formaldehyde gas from plywood and MDF.

4.3
00:01:06.772 --> 00:01:12.120
The World Health Organisation says formaldehyde can be very harmful for your health — reports link it to cancer.

4.4
00:01:12.120 --> 00:01:17.468
Deliver that slowly.

4.5
00:01:17.468 --> 00:01:22.816
It matters.

5.1
00:01:22.816 --> 00:01:28.281
Never quote before qualifying.

5.2
00:01:28.281 --> 00:01:33.747
Ask: are you looking at a premium wellness solution, or comparing with basic carpentry?

5.3
00:01:33.747 --> 00:01:39.212
Magppie is not in the carpentry segment — say it kindly, and say it early.

6.1
00:01:39.212 --> 00:01:45.411
Then the range: eighty-four hundred to ten thousand eight hundred rupees per square foot, by finish.

6.2
00:01:45.411 --> 00:01:51.610
A ten-by-ten kitchen typically lands between twelve and fifteen lakhs.

6.3
00:01:51.610 --> 00:01:57.809
Check alignment — does this range fit what you're considering?

6.4
00:01:57.809 --> 00:02:04.008
— then close on the layout: share your kitchen layout, and we'll prepare a customised estimate on WhatsApp.

7.1
00:02:04.008 --> 00:02:20.836
In the showroom the same logic wears different clothes: re-qualify the visitor, reframe the category, walk the material science live, justify the premium, frame the fifteen-year value — then pricing, terms, and closure intent.

8.1
00:02:20.836 --> 00:02:26.784
Your notes.

8.2
00:02:26.784 --> 00:02:32.732
One — eight stages: open, discover, agitate, solution, deep dive, budget, price, next step.

8.3
00:02:32.732 --> 00:02:38.680
Two — qualify the budget before any number: Magppie is not in the carpentry segment.

8.4
00:02:38.680 --> 00:02:44.628
Three — the range is eighty-four hundred to ten thousand eight hundred per square foot.

8.5
00:02:44.628 --> 00:02:50.576
Four — always close on the layout: customised estimate on WhatsApp.

9.1
00:02:50.576 --> 00:02:53.374
Same flow, every channel.

9.2
00:02:53.374 --> 00:02:56.172
Take the quiz.

